CSS Colors
Express color by specifying the amount of RDGRBL that should be present
Common way
	RGB
		Red: 0-255
		Green: 0-255
		Blue: 0-255
		Example Magenta
			body {
			   background-color: rgb(255, 0, 255);
			}
	Hexedecimal (in decimal) 
		Red: 00-FF
		Green: 00-FF
		Blue: 00-FF
		Example Magenta
			body {
			   background-color: #ff00ff;
			}
helpful to use a color picker

Exercise Which CSS declarations can beused to represent the standard color for blue?
1. color: #ff0000;
2. color: blue;
3. color: rgb(0, 0, 255);
4. color: #ffff00
5. color: #00f;
Answers: 2, 3, 5
